During a meeting with G7 leaders, the President stated that the mission in Kabul will end once objectives are achieved. The current plan is to finish by August 31st, with progress being made in evacuating Americans, third-country nationals, and Afghan allies. The President acknowledged the increasing risk to troops from ISIS-K and emphasized the need for continued coordination with the Taliban for evacuee access to the airport. Contingency plans are being requested in case the timeline needs to be adjusted.